{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 05:07:33.722989", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nAssessment summary\n- Status: Network is not forwarding tenant traffic. Severe control-plane issue detected.\n- Scope of impact: All hosts, including those on the same leaf, are unable to reach each other.\n\nKey symptoms and tests\n- Host reachability:\n  - host_1_1 → host_1_2 (10.0.0.1 → 10.0.0.2): Destination Host Unreachable, 100% loss.\n  - host_1_1 → host_2_1 (10.0.0.1 → 10.0.0.9): Destination Host Unreachable, 100% loss.\n  - host_2_1 → host_2_2 (10.0.0.9 → 10.0.0.10): Destination Host Unreachable, 100% loss.\n  - Interpretation: Even intra-leaf L2 forwarding is not occurring; ARP is not being flooded/learned.\n- Switch Open vSwitch (OVS) state:\n  - All switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) have fail_mode: secure.\n  - Flow tables are empty on all switches (ovs-ofctl dump-flows).\n  - Ports appear up and LIVE at 10G on all switches (ovs-ofctl show), indicating no physical link issues.\n- Controller connectivity:\n  - Controller target on each switch: tcp:20.0.0.100:6633.\n  - ovs-vsctl list controller shows is_connected: false on all three switches with last_error=\"Connection timed out\", state BACKOFF/CONNECTING.\n  - Management network reachability is OK at L3: each switch can ping 20.0.0.100 successfully.\n  - Interpretation: IP reachability to the controller host exists, but the OpenFlow TCP service is not reachable/listening on port 6633 (or blocked), so OVS cannot establish sessions.\n\nLocalization of fault\n- Data plane links and switch ports: Healthy (ports LIVE, no errors, physical connectivity looks good).\n- Host configuration: IPs and routes are correct for 10.0.0.0/24; failures are consistent with ARP not being bridged.\n- Control plane: The SDN controller endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633 is not accepting OpenFlow TCP connections from all switches. This is the common point of failure affecting the entire fabric.\n\nRoot cause\n- The OVS instances cannot establish OpenFlow sessions to 20.0.0.100:6633 (TCP connect timeouts), despite layer-3 reachability to 20.0.0.100. As a result, with fail_mode=secure and empty flow tables, switches drop all traffic, including ARP, causing complete loss of host-to-host connectivity.\n- Likely reasons at the controller side include: controller service down or not listening on TCP port 6633, or a policy/firewall blocking that port. The exact controller-side condition is not directly observable from the provided environment, but the consistent TCP timeout evidence across all switches isolates the issue to that endpoint/port.\n\nRelevant evidence\n- Host pings: 100% loss with “Destination Host Unreachable” from the source IP.\n- ovs-vsctl list controller (all switches): is_connected=false; last_error=\"Connection timed out\"; state BACKOFF/CONNECTING; target \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\".\n- ovs-ofctl show: All data ports LIVE; local ports down (expected); indicates physical health.\n- ovs-ofctl dump-flows: Empty on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1.\n- Switch management network: leaf_1 (20.0.0.5), leaf_2 (20.0.0.6), spine_1 (20.0.0.1) can ping 20.0.0.100 with 0% loss.\n\nConclusion\n- Anomaly: Yes — complete control-plane outage to the SDN controller’s OpenFlow port.\n- Fault localization: Controller endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633 (or an intervening filter), not the switch ports or host configs.\n- Root cause: OpenFlow TCP service unreachable from all switches, leaving OVS in secure mode with empty flow tables and resulting in a total data-plane forwarding failure.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 23365, "output_tokens": 3283, "total_tokens": 26648, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 19328}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2368}}}
